<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4">Single-Arm Dumbbell Row</h3>



<p>The Single-Arm Dumbbell Row is a fundamental strength-training exercise that primarily targets the muscles in your upper back, including the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, and trapezius. This exercise involves lifting a dumbbell with one hand while supporting your body with the opposite leg and hand on a bench, effectively isolating and strengthening the targeted muscle groups. </p>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-single-arm-bent-over-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Single-arm dumbbell rows</a> are excellent for building back strength, improving posture, and enhancing overall upper-body muscular balance. Proper form and controlled movements are essential to reap the full benefits of this exercise while minimizing the risk of injury.</p>



