<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What muscles do lat pulldown alternative exercises work?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">In addition to the latissimus dorsi, these pulling exercises also target muscles in your upper back including your rhomboids, traps, and rear deltoids. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1705654509864"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What if I can’t do a pull-up on my own?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">You can use resistance bands tied to a sturdy bar and then loop them under your feet for assisted pull-ups. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1705654510582"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How do I know if I have adequate range of motion for these exercises?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">To be completely sure you have good mobility to complete these exercises, consult a physical therapist or personal trainer.</p> </div> </div>
